Lagos State All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftain Olasupo Olowe has said Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, the party’s presidential candidate, will in next year’s election. He spoke while mobilising residents of Kosofe Local Government to register in the Continuous Voter Registration undertaken by Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). The party chieftain said the mobilisation was to ensure his supporters got their PVCs to vote Tinubu and other APC candidates.   Police recruitment based on merit, not politics,…     Buhari celebrates Amusan, Brume over World Athletics feats     FCT taskforce begins massive demolition of…   “In every election, no one can ignore the power of the thumb. It is the magic to herald victory, thus in our beloved country, the importance of PVCs is critical to achieving a huge victory for Asiwaju Tinubu. “Thus, I have decided to invest my time in moving from one house to another to mobilise Nigerians to register and be involved in the Asiwaju project,” he said. Olowe said Shettima as running mate was a perfect material to complement the nationwide acceptability of Tinubu.